      <div class="msgContentFrame">I have seen a lot of Gladiators complain about the lack of accuracy on this class. <br />As I've complained about this myself, let me explain why this usually happens. <br /> <br />A lot of gladiators switch to &quot;Ash Machuitl&quot; (the wooden spanking bat weapon) at a certain point during their lvling. The problem with that damn weapon is, that it has a gimped accuracy, it's totally worthless piece of wood and will just make you look like a damn fool swinging arround that thing, while missing every damn swing. <br /> <br />So to all those Gladiators that r still having problems hitting stuff, please switch to a dagger arround your class rank or higher, or get any kind of sword, just stay away from those wooden things. <br /> <br />Ooooh, and if you'r still missing quite a bit even with a dagger, grab some accuracy rings. <br />And add your dex to 60  <br />(from some not very accurate tests it seems that 60 dex is a sweet spot as of right now, where dex has a decent (a few %) positive overall effects, on accuracy, crit and evasion)</div>
