      <div class="msgContentFrame">thats because the acc stats on all the baseball bat weapons is horrible compared to the swords/daggers XD <br /> <br />&quot;It's like if a mob is standing on some spot you just can't hit propperly untill you move closer/further to the mob or slightly to the side etc.&quot; <br /> <br />err that's more of a perception issue. The game only recognizes front/rear/left/right directions when it comes to accuracy. Distance has no effect on accuracy either..if you within your class' range to hit the game will animate you striking or jumping forward to strike if you a bit father away than the default combat attack animation is set to. You can check this is true by noticing how shield users will jump forward to 'block' an attack by a mob...its the game tossing your character into a default animation position with the npc.  <br /> <br />Height is not recognized by the game at all, rather the message that 'target is too low' (which happens even when it is YOU who is lower than the mob) is a line-of-sight check.</div>
