      <div class="msgContentFrame">You have to look at all the stats when getting a weapon. Not one of them. The dagger has gimped attack. So you will hit more, but be doing less damage. The dagger's highest stat is parry rate, which is pretty much useless for a Gladiator (I have my shield up 95% of the time). <br /> <br />Daggers look to follow a stat allotment like: Parry&gt;Crit&gt;Accuracy&gt;Attack. <br />While the Macuahuitl follow something like: Crit&gt;Accuracy&gt;Attack&gt;Parry. <br /> <br />You have to weigh what you want more from your character, do you want more damage, more parry, more accuracy? Personally, the daggers do crap damage, and their accuracy is not that much better (except for the few levels where they are in range of you &quot;optimal level&quot;). But all in all, the swords seem to have lower parry rates, and higher damage. I personally try to use the weapon with the lowest parry rate possible, as again, its a totally worthless stat for a sword and board tank.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1385155" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=1385155">[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/7865_7d8fe305bfae897b.png</a>[/img]</a></div></div>
